PGE, PGNiG, Dalkia Are Among SPEC Bidders, Rzeczpospolita Says

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-04-21T04:35:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/pge-pgnig-dalkia-are-among-spec-bidders-rzeczpospolita-says.html
PGE SA, Poland’s biggest utility,
and  Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA (PGN) , the gas company
known as PGNiG, are among bidders shortlisted by the city of
Warsaw to buy its heat distributor SPEC SA, Rzeczpospolita
reported, without saying where it got the information.   France ’s Dalkia SA and Penta Investments Ltd. of the  Czech
Republic  are also on the list, which isn’t “much shorter” than
the one containing between 10 and 20 companies that last month
placed initial bids, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
